other_tests.findings: Normal trilineage hematopoiesis with approximately 20% plasma cells, diagnostic of multiple myeloma.

Normal concentrations of protein in the albumin and in the alpha 1, alpha 2, and beta regions; a single spike within the gamma region accounting for a concentration of 1.91 g per deciliter; confirmed presence of IgG kappa monoclonal gammopathy.

other_tests.procedure_name: Mixing test for activated partial-thromboplastin time
other_tests.findings: Activated partial-thromboplastin time returned to normal after mixing with normal plasma, suggesting a factor deficiency.
